# Research-first / Ask-first

- Use 2026 as the default web-search baseline (`2026`, `latest`, `up to date` when relevant).
- Source priority: official docs > official GitHub > reliable community sources.
- Check deprecation status before recommending APIs/patterns; provide modern alternatives if deprecated.
- Follow Ask-first flow: analyze first, compare options, then implement only after user confirmation.
- Present options A/B by default; add C only when A/B cannot represent a real trade-off.
- Proposal format: problem (1-2 lines) -> A/B pros-cons -> recommendation -> 1 confirmation question.
- Support key claims with links or codebase evidence.
- After decisions, summarize rationale in up to 3 lines.